---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Types of Eclipses - Eclipse Central" description="Learn about the different types of eclipses: solar, lunar, partial, and total eclipses.">
  <article class="page-content">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Types of Eclipses</h1>
      <p class="page-intro">Understanding the different types of eclipses and what makes each one special.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="eclipse-type">
      <h2>ðŸŒž Solar Eclipses</h2>
      <p>Solar eclipses occur when the Moon passes between Earth and the Sun, casting a shadow on Earth.</p>
      
      <div class="subtypes">
        <div class="subtype-card">
          <h3>Total Solar Eclipse</h3>
          <p>The Moon completely covers the Sun's disk, revealing the Sun's corona. Day turns to night for a few minutes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="subtype-card">
          <h3>Partial Solar Eclipse</h3>
          <p>The Moon only partially covers the Sun, creating a crescent-shaped Sun visible from Earth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="subtype-card">
          <h3>Annular Solar Eclipse</h3>
          <p>The Moon appears smaller than the Sun, creating a "ring of fire" effect around the Moon's silhouette.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="eclipse-type">
      <h2>ðŸŒ• Lunar Eclipses</h2>
      <p>Lunar eclipses happen when Earth passes between the Sun and Moon, casting Earth's shadow on the Moon.</p>
      
      <div class="subtypes">
        <div class="subtype-card">
          <h3>Total Lunar Eclipse</h3>
          <p>The Moon passes completely through Earth's shadow, often appearing red or copper-colored.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="subtype-card">
          <h3>Partial Lunar Eclipse</h3>
          <p>Only part of the Moon passes through Earth's shadow, creating a partial darkening effect.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="subtype-card">
          <h3>Penumbral Lunar Eclipse</h3>
          <p>The Moon passes through Earth's outer shadow, causing a subtle dimming that's harder to notice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="frequency">
      <h2>ðŸ“Š Eclipse Frequency</h2>
      <div class="frequency-grid">
        <div class="frequency-item">
          <h4>Solar Eclipses</h4>
          <p>2-5 per year globally<br>~375 years between total eclipses at same location</p>
        </div>
        <div class="frequency-item">
          <h4>Lunar Eclipses</h4>
          <p>2-3 per year globally<br>Visible from entire night side of Earth</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-content {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: var(--space-8) 0;
  }

  .page-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .page-intro {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }

  .eclipse-type {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
  }

  .eclipse-type h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
  }

  .eclipse-type > p {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
  }

  .subtypes {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-4);
  }

  .subtype-card {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
  }

  .subtype-card h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .frequency {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    padding: var(--space-8);
    border-radius: var(--border-radius);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  }

  .frequency h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-2xl);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    text-align: center;
  }

  .frequency-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-6);
  }

  .frequency-item {
    text-align: center;
    padding: var(--space-4);
  }

  .frequency-item h4 {
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .subtypes {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    }
  }
</style>